children.subject: For #2, the student answer doesn’t say that while it is possible to enroll on CalCentral, the final exams will be at the same time, and it will be your problem to make sure to that one of the courses is offering an alternate final. Don’t assume that they will.

history.content:
1.) Does Linguis 100 count for an EECS technical elective?

2.) Also, I heard that EECS classes can now be taken even if they conflict with one another. For example, say I enroll in Linguis 100 and then immediately afterwards I enroll in EE16B which happens to have the same lecture time. Is this possible for me to do that now?
history.subject: Linguistics 100 and Course Conflicts: A Two Part Question
